('COM620101', 'LINEAR ALGEBRA', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Linear algebra is a branch of mathematics that deals with the study of vectors, vector spaces, and linear transformations. It is an important subject for computer science because it provides the mathematical foundations for many areas in computer graphics, machine learning, and artificial intelligence.', 2, 0, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 04:51:20', '2023-01-20 04:51:20'),
('COM620102', 'ENGLISH', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'English study is the process of acquiring knowledge and skills in the English language. This can include studying grammar, vocabulary, reading, writing, speaking, and listening, as well as more specialized areas such as English for academic purposes, business English, or English for specific fields such as medicine or law. The goal of English study is to improve fluency, comprehension, and communication skills in the language.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 04:56:01', '2023-01-20 04:56:01'),
('COM620103', 'PROGRAMMING BASICS', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Programming is the process of designing and creating instructions, also known as code, that can be executed by a computer. These instructions tell the computer what to do, such as performing calculations, making decisions, and controlling the flow of a program. Basic programming concepts include data types, variables, functions, control structures, and algorithms. Additionally, a student should have a general understanding of how computers work, including concepts like memory and storage, and how programs are executed by the computer.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 04:57:37', '2023-01-20 04:59:31'),
('COM620104', 'LOGIC', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Logic is the study of reasoning and argumentation, and it is a fundamental concept in computer science. In computer science, logic is used to model the behavior of computing systems and to reason about the correctness of algorithms and programs. Logic plays a central role in the study of computer science, providing a formal and mathematical framework for reasoning about the properties of computing systems and for designing correct and efficient algorithms. Additionally, a student should have a strong understanding of the foundations of computer science, including the concept of computation and what can be computed by a computer. They should also have a solid understanding of the relationship between logic and other branches of computer science, such as theoretical computer science and computer engineering.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 04:59:21', '2023-01-20 04:59:21'),
('COM620105', 'MATHEMATICS', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Mathematics plays a crucial role in computer science. It provides the foundation for understanding many of the theoretical concepts in the field, and it is used to design and analyze algorithms and data structures. A strong background in mathematics is essential for computer scientists to understand the theoretical foundations of the field, as well as for solving practical problems in areas such as algorithm design, machine learning and artificial intelligence. Students should be able to apply mathematical concepts to solve problems in computer science, such as designing and analyzing algorithms and data structures. They should also be able to read and understand mathematical proofs, and be able to communicate their own mathematical reasoning clearly and rigorously.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 05:00:29', '2023-01-20 05:00:29'),
('COM620106', 'STATISTICS AND PROBABILITY', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'A statistics and probabilistics study is an area of study that involves the collection, analysis, interpretation, presentation, and understanding of numerical data. It encompasses both the theory and applications of statistics and probabilistic reasoning in areas such as science, engineering, medicine, finance, and social sciences.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 05:01:31', '2023-01-20 05:01:31'),
('COM620107', 'DISCRETE MATHEMATICS', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Discrete Mathematics is a branch of mathematics that deals with the study of discrete structures and their properties. These structures include sets, relations, functions, graphs, and algorithms, among others. The course covers topics such as combinatorics, number theory, logic, algebra, and graph theory. Discrete mathematics is essential for the understanding of computer science, as well as in areas such as operations research, cryptography, and network design. The course is designed to develop the students\' ability to think abstractly, to apply mathematical reasoning, and to solve problems using mathematical models.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 05:21:27', '2023-01-20 05:21:27'),
('COM620108', 'STRUCTURED PROGRAMMING', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Structured programming is a course that focuses on the use of logical and systematic methods for designing, coding, and testing computer programs. The course covers the fundamental concepts and techniques of structured programming, including the use of  functions, and subroutines. Students learn how to design and implement programs that are well-organized, easy to understand, and maintainable. The course also covers debugging and testing techniques to ensure that programs are free from errors and bugs. By the end of the course, students will have the knowledge and skills to create structured, efficient, and reliable programs using a variety of programming languages.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 05:22:41', '2023-01-20 05:22:41'),
('COM620109', 'INTRODUCTION TO COMPUTER ORGANIZATION', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Introduction to Computer Organization is a course that provides an overview of the fundamental concepts and principles of computer architecture and organization. The course covers topics such as computer components and their interactions, data representation and manipulation, instruction sets, memory hierarchy, and input/output systems. Students will learn about the basic structure and operation of computer systems, and how the various components work together to perform tasks. They will also learn about the different types of computer systems, including mainframes, workstations, and personal computers. The course aims to provide students with a solid understanding of computer organization and architecture, and how these concepts are applied in real-world scenarios.', 2, 0, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 05:23:59', '2023-01-20 05:23:59'),
('COM620110', 'INTRODUCTION TO INFORMATION SYSTEMS', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Introduction to Information Systems is a course that provides students with an overview of the different systems and technologies used in the field of information management. The course covers the basics of information systems, including their functions, components, and applications. Students will learn about the different types of information systems, including management information systems, decision support systems, and expert systems. They will also learn about the role of information systems in organizations, including how they are used to support decision-making, manage data and information, and improve overall performance. The course also covers the latest trends and developments in information systems, such as cloud computing, mobile technologies, and big data analytics. Throughout the course, students will gain an understanding of the impact that information systems have on organizations and society as a whole.', 2, 0, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 05:24:48', '2023-01-20 05:24:48'),
('COM620111', 'SOFTWARE ENGINEERING', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Software Engineering is a course that focuses on the process of designing, developing, testing and maintaining software. It covers the entire lifecycle of software development, including requirements analysis, design, implementation, testing and maintenance. The course covers both theoretical and practical aspects of software engineering, with a focus on the use of industry-standard tools and techniques for software development. Students will learn about object-oriented programming, design patterns, software testing, software project management, and software architecture. The course also covers the latest trends in software engineering such as Agile development, DevOps, and software as a service (SaaS). The course is designed to equip students with the knowledge and skills necessary to become successful software engineers in the industry.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 05:25:44', '2023-01-20 05:25:44'),
('COM620112', 'OPERATION SYSTEM', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'An Operating System (OS) course is a comprehensive study of the fundamental concepts, principles and techniques of operating systems. The course covers the design and implementation of various types of operating systems such as single-user, multi-user, and distributed systems. Students will learn about the different components of an operating system such as the kernel, process management, memory management, file systems, and security. They will also explore the different algorithms and techniques used to implement these components, such as scheduling, paging, and virtual memory. The course will also cover the different types of operating systems such as Windows, Linux, and Unix. Students will learn about the architecture and design of these operating systems and the differences between them. They will also gain hands-on experience with programming and debugging operating systems, using various tools and techniques.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 05:27:26', '2023-01-20 05:27:26'),
('COM620113', 'DATA STRUCTURE AND ALGORITHM', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Data Structure and Algorithm is a course that focuses on the fundamental concepts and techniques used to design and analyze algorithms and data structures. The course covers a wide range of topics, including basic data structures such as arrays, linked lists, stacks, queues, and trees, as well as advanced algorithms for searching, sorting, and graph traversal. Throughout the course, students will learn how to use these data structures and algorithms in real-world applications and will gain an understanding of the trade-offs involved in choosing the right data structure or algorithm for a particular problem. The course will also cover the analysis of algorithms and the use of big O notation to evaluate the time and space complexity of an algorithm.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 05:28:12', '2023-01-20 05:28:12'),
('COM620201', 'NUMERICAL ANALYSIS', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Numerical analysis is a branch of mathematics that deals with the design, analysis, and implementation of algorithms for approximating solutions to problems involving continuous variables, such as those arising in engineering, science, and finance. It uses a variety of mathematical techniques, including calculus, linear algebra, and optimization, to design and analyze algorithms that can be implemented on computers to solve a wide range of problems. Some common areas of study in numerical analysis include numerical linear algebra, numerical optimization, numerical integration and differentiation, and the solution of differential equations. In order for students to be competent in the field of numerical analysis, they should possess a solid understanding of the mathematical concepts and techniques used to solve mathematical problems using numerical methods.', 2, 0, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 05:30:27', '2023-01-20 05:30:27'),
('COM620202', 'DATABASE', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'A database is a structured collection of data that is stored electronically, and can be accessed and managed by computer software. The data in a database is usually organized in a logical, orderly manner, making it easy to find and retrieve specific information. There are many different types of databases, including relational databases, document databases, and graph databases, but they all serve the same basic purpose of storing and managing data. A student who is proficient in databases should have a solid understanding of the concepts and principles that underlie the design, implementation, and management of databases.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 05:31:22', '2023-01-20 05:31:22'),
('COM620203', 'ALGORITHM DESIGN AND ANALYSIS', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Algorithm design and analysis is the process of creating, analyzing and evaluating algorithms. An algorithm is a step-by-step procedure for solving a problem or achieving a specific task. Algorithm design and analysis is an important part of computer science and is used to make sure that algorithms are as efficient as possible and to find the best algorithm for a specific problem. A student who is proficient in algorithm design and analysis should have a strong understanding of the concepts and principles that underlie the creation and analysis of algorithms. This includes knowledge of the various techniques and methods that are used to design and analyze algorithms, as well as an understanding of the trade-offs that are involved.', 2, 0, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 05:32:00', '2023-01-20 05:32:00'),
('COM620204', 'COMMUNICATION AND PRESENTATION', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Communication is the process of exchanging information through the transmission of messages. It can take place verbally, through writing, or through nonverbal means such as body language or tone of voice. Communication can be one-way, in which case it is called a monologue, or two-way, in which case it is called a dialogue. Student competency in communication and presentation refers to the ability of a student to effectively communicate and present information to others in a clear, organized, and engaging manner. A student who is competent in communication and presentation is able to convey ideas, arguments, and data in a way that is easy to understand and that holds the audience\'s attention.', 1, 0, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 05:32:48', '2023-01-20 05:32:48'),
('COM620205', 'DATA COMMUNICATION AND COMPUTER NETWORK', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Data communication is the process of transmitting digital information from one device to another. It enables the transfer of data between computers, servers, and other digital devices. Data communication uses various technologies and protocols to transmit data, such as wired and wireless communication methods.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 05:33:46', '2023-01-20 05:33:46'),
('COM620206', 'OBJECT ORIENTED PROGRAMMING', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) is a programming paradigm that focuses on the use of objects and their interactions to create software. It is a method of organizing and structuring code that allows for more efficient and maintainable software development. In this course, students will learn the basic concepts of OOP, such as encapsulation, inheritance, and polymorphism. They will also learn how to design and implement object-oriented systems using a popular programming language such as Java or Python. The course will begin with an introduction to the basics of OOP, including classes, objects, and methods. Students will then learn how to use inheritance and polymorphism to create more complex and reusable code. They will also learn how to use encapsulation to protect the data and behavior of their objects. Throughout the course, students will work on practical exercises and projects to gain hands-on experience in creating and designing object-oriented systems. They will also learn how to debug and troubleshoot common OOP issues. By the end of the course, students will have a solid understanding of the principles of OOP and will be able to apply them to real-world software development projects.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 05:34:37', '2023-01-20 05:34:37'),
('COM620207', 'INTRODUCTION TO DIGITAL SYSTEMS', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, '\"Introduction to Digital Systems is a course that provides a comprehensive overview of the fundamental concepts and principles of digital systems. The course covers topics such as digital logic gates, Boolean algebra, combinatorial and sequential circuits, and computer architecture. The course starts with an introduction to digital electronics, including basic concepts such as binary numbers, Boolean algebra, and logic gates. Students will learn how to design and implement simple digital circuits using various types of logic gates, including AND, OR, NOT, and NAND gates. The course then moves on to combinatorial circuits, where students will learn how to design circuits that perform specific logical operations. This includes learning about multiplexers, demultiplexers, encoders, and decoders.\r\n\r\n\"', 2, 0, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 05:35:53', '2023-01-20 05:35:53'),
('COM620208', 'LANGUAGE AND AUTOMATA THEORY', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, '\"Language and Automata Theory is a course that explores the foundations of theoretical computer science. It covers the basic concepts of formal languages and the automata that accept them. The course begins with an introduction to the formal languages, including regular expressions, context-free languages, and Turing machines. It then covers the theory of automata, including finite automata, pushdown automata, and Turing machines. The course also covers the formal models used to represent languages and automata, including regular expressions, context-free grammars, and Turing machines. It examines the properties of these models and the relationships between them.\r\n\r\n\"', 2, 0, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 05:48:09', '2023-01-20 05:48:09'),
('COM620209', 'E-SERVICES', 'Peminatan', 'Tidak ada', 2020, '\"other digital platforms. Students will learn about the different types of e-services, such as e-commerce, e-health, and e-government, and how they are used in different sectors. The course begins with an introduction to e-services and the various technologies used to deliver them. Students will learn about the characteristics of e-services, including interactivity, personalization, and customization. They will also learn about the various e-service models, such as B2C and B2B. The course then covers the different types of e-services, including e-commerce, e-health, and e-government. Students will learn about the benefits of each type of e-service, as well as the challenges and risks associated with them. They will also learn about the different platforms and technologies used to deliver e-services, such as web portals, mobile apps, and cloud services. Throughout the course, students will be required to complete a variety of hands-on projects, such as creating an e-commerce website, designing an e-health app, or developing an e-government system. These projects will help students apply the concepts they have learned in the classroom to real-world situations.\r\n\r\n\"', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 05:49:57', '2023-01-20 05:49:57'),
('COM620210', 'MULTIMEDIA', 'Peminatan', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Multimedia is a course that teaches students about the various forms of media and how to effectively use them in creative projects. This course covers a wide range of topics, including video production, audio recording and editing, graphic design, and web design. Throughout the course, students will learn about the technical aspects of each medium and how to use different software and tools to create their projects. They will also learn about the creative side of multimedia, including storytelling, composition, and visual aesthetics.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 05:51:45', '2023-01-20 05:51:45'),
('COM620211', 'INTERPRETER PROGRAMMING', 'Peminatan', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Interpreter Programming is a course that focuses on the design and implementation of software that is used to translate or interpret source code written in one programming language into another programming language. The course covers the different types of interpreters, such as command-line interpreters and script interpreters, and the programming languages and technologies used to create them. Throughout the course, students will learn about the theory and practice of interpreter design, including the principles of lexical analysis, parsing, and code generation. They will also learn how to design and implement interpreters for different types of programming languages and environments, such as high-level languages and embedded systems. The course also covers the use of different tools and libraries for interpreter development, such as lexers, parsers, and code generators. Students will learn how to use these tools to create interpreters that are efficient, maintainable, and easy to use.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 05:52:29', '2023-01-20 05:52:29'),
('COM620212', 'SOFTWARE TESTING', 'Peminatan', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Software testing is a course that teaches students how to test and evaluate software applications and systems to ensure they are functioning properly and meeting the requirements of the user. This course covers a range of testing techniques, including manual testing, automated testing, and performance testing, as well as the tools and methods used in each method. Students will learn how to create test plans, test cases, and test scripts, and how to execute and report on testing results. They will also learn how to identify and troubleshoot defects in software, and how to work with development teams to ensure that the software is of high quality. Additionally, students will gain hands-on experience in applying testing methodologies and tools to real-world software projects, and will have the opportunity to develop skills that are in high demand in the software industry.', 2, 0, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 05:53:12', '2023-01-20 05:53:12'),
('COM620213', 'ANALYSIS AND DESIGN OF INFORMATION SYSTEMS', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'The Analysis and Design of Information Systems (ADIS) is a course that typically covers the principles and techniques used in the development of information systems. The focus of the course is on the systematic and structured process of understanding the needs of an organization and translating those needs into functional and technical specifications for an information system.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 05:54:19', '2023-01-20 05:54:19'),
('COM620214', 'ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Artificial Intelligence (AI) is a course that explores the use of computational techniques to simulate and replicate human intelligence. It covers a range of topics such as natural language processing, machine learning, computer vision, and robotics. Students will learn about various AI algorithms and techniques, including neural networks, decision trees, and genetic algorithms, as well as how to apply these techniques to real-world problems. The course also examines the ethical and societal implications of AI and its potential impact on society.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 05:54:59', '2023-01-20 05:54:59'),
('COM620215', 'FIELD STUDY', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Field study is a course that typically combines hands-on, experiential learning with theoretical concepts in a specific field of study. Students engage in research, observation, and analysis of real-world settings, such as businesses, organizations, or natural environments. The course focuses on the application of knowledge and skills to real-world problems and situations. It may include field trips, interviews, and case studies, as well as projects and assignments that require students to collect and analyze data in the field.', 0, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 05:58:20', '2023-01-20 05:58:20'),
('COM620216', 'MOBILE TECHNOLOGY AND APPLICATIONS', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Mobile Technology and Applications is a course that explores the current and emerging technologies used in mobile devices and applications. The course covers the fundamental concepts and principles of mobile technology, including the architecture and operation of mobile devices, mobile networks and wireless communications, mobile operating systems, and mobile applications development. Students will learn about the latest trends and innovations in mobile technology.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 05:59:19', '2023-01-20 05:59:19'),
('COM620217', 'INFORMATION THEORY', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Information Theory is a branch of mathematics that deals with the quantification, storage, and communication of information. It encompasses a wide range of topics, including data compression, error correction, entropy, information capacity, and cryptography. Students in a course on Information Theory will learn about the mathematical foundations of these concepts, as well as their practical applications in real-world systems. The course may also include hands-on experience with coding and decoding algorithms, and the use of software tools for information processing.', 2, 0, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 06:00:20', '2023-01-20 06:00:20'),
('COM620218', 'INTERNET OF THINGS', 'Peminatan', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'The Internet of Things (IoT) subject course is a multidisciplinary field that explores the integration of connected devices and sensors with the internet to create smart systems and applications. This course covers the technical and practical aspects of IoT, including the design, implementation, and deployment of IoT systems. It covers topics such as IoT device hardware and software, network protocols, data management, and security. The course also explores the use of IoT in various industries, including healthcare, transportation, energy, and manufacturing. Students will gain hands-on experience with IoT technologies and will be able to design and implement their own IoT projects. The course aims to prepare students for the rapidly-evolving field of IoT and the opportunities it presents for innovation and automation.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 06:01:03', '2023-01-20 06:01:03'),
('COM620219', 'WEB PROGRAMMING', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Web Programming is a course that teaches students the fundamentals of creating and maintaining websites using programming languages such as HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. The course covers the basics of web design and layout, as well as more advanced topics such as dynamic content, server-side scripting, and database integration. Students will learn to create interactive and responsive websites that can be accessed from any device and will be able to understand the basics of web development. The course will also touch on web design principles and best practices for creating and maintaining a website, making it an excellent choice for anyone looking to create a website for personal or business use. The course will be taught in a hands-on and interactive format, allowing students to apply their knowledge as they learn.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 06:10:20', '2023-01-20 06:10:20'),
('COM620220', 'DISTRIBUTED DATA PROCESSING', 'Peminatan', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Distributed data processing is a course that focuses on the principles and practices of designing, implementing, and managing distributed systems for processing large amounts of data. It covers topics such as distributed computing architectures, data storage and retrieval systems, data replication and consistency, data partitioning and mapping, and parallel and distributed algorithms. The course also explores the challenges and trade-offs associated with distributed data processing, including scalability, fault tolerance, and security. Students will learn how to design and implement distributed systems using programming languages such as Java, Python, and MapReduce. They will also gain hands-on experience with distributed data processing tools such as Hadoop, Spark, and Cassandra. Overall, this course equips students with the skills and knowledge necessary to design, build, and manage distributed data processing systems in a variety of settings.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 06:11:30', '2023-01-20 06:11:30'),
('COM620221', 'DECLARATION PROGRAMMING', 'Peminatan', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Declaration Programming is a course that focuses on the fundamental concepts of computer programming, including data types, variables, control structures, and functions. Students will learn how to create and manipulate variables, use control structures such as loops and conditionals, and write and call functions. The course will also cover basic data structures such as arrays and lists, and will provide an introduction to the logic and reasoning behind programming. Additionally, the course may delve into some specific programming languages such as Python, C++ or Java. Students will gain hands-on experience by working on various programming projects throughout the course. The course is suitable for anyone with an interest in learning how to code, regardless of prior experience.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 06:12:25', '2023-01-20 06:12:25'),
('COM620222', 'MACHINE LEARNING', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Machine Learning is a branch of Artificial Intelligence that deals with the development of algorithms and statistical models that enable computers to learn from and make predictions or decisions without explicit instructions. The course typically covers the fundamental concepts and techniques of machine learning, including supervised learning, unsupervised learning, and reinforcement learning. Topics covered may include linear regression, decision trees, k-nearest neighbors, support vector machines, neural networks, and deep learning. The course may also include practical applications of machine learning in various domains, such as computer vision, natural language processing, and predictive modeling. Students will learn how to implement machine learning algorithms in programming languages such as Python or R and use libraries and frameworks such as TensorFlow, Scikit-learn, and Keras.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 06:13:13', '2023-01-20 06:13:13'),
('COM620223', 'KNOWLEDGE MANAGEMENT', 'Peminatan', 'Tidak ada', 2020, '\"Knowledge Management is a course that focuses on the acquisition, organization, and dissemination of knowledge within an organization. The subject covers various concepts and techniques that are used to manage and leverage the organization\'s knowledge assets. These concepts include knowledge creation, knowledge sharing, knowledge retention, and knowledge governance. The course also covers the use of technology and other tools to support knowledge management, such as knowledge management systems, collaboration platforms, and data analytics. Additionally, the course explores the role of culture, leadership, and change management in knowledge management, as well as the ethical considerations associated with managing knowledge. The course is designed for students who are interested in understanding how organizations can use knowledge to gain competitive advantages and improve decision-making.\r\n\r\n\"', 2, 0, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 06:14:23', '2023-01-20 06:14:23'),
('COM620301', 'ENTREPRENEURSHIP', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Entrepreneurship is an undergraduate subject that teaches the skills and knowledge to start and grow businesses, using hands-on approaches such as case studies, real-world examples, and practical exercises. It covers key aspects such as identifying opportunities, creating business plans, managing finances, and leading teams. The program also emphasizes on innovation and creativity and includes mentorship, internship, and real-world experience opportunities, to gain a complete understanding of starting a business and the legal and regulatory environment it operates in.', 2, 0, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 06:15:07', '2023-01-20 06:15:07'),
('COM620302', 'RESEARCH METHODOLOGY', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Research Methodology is a course that focuses on the principles and techniques used to conduct research in various fields. It covers a wide range of topics, including the design and execution of research studies, the selection and use of appropriate research methods, and the analysis and interpretation of data. The course also covers the ethical and legal considerations involved in research, as well as the process of writing and publishing research papers. Students will learn how to develop a research question, design a study, collect and analyze data, and communicate the findings to a wider audience. Through hands-on activities and assignments, students will develop the skills and knowledge necessary to conduct independent research projects. This course is essential for students who plan to pursue careers in research or academia, as well as for those interested in understanding the scientific process.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 06:15:48', '2023-01-20 06:15:48'),
('COM620303', 'PANCASILA EDUCATION', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Pancasila Education is a course that focuses on the study and implementation of the principles of Pancasila, which is the national philosophy of Indonesia. The course covers the historical, philosophical, and socio-political context of Pancasila, as well as its role in shaping the national identity and culture of Indonesia. Students in this course will learn about the five pillars of Pancasila: belief in one God, just and civilized humanity, the unity of Indonesia, democracy through deliberation and consensus, and social justice for all. They will also study the ways in which Pancasila is implemented in the education system and in various aspects of society, such as politics and the legal system. Throughout the course, students will engage in critical discussions, debates, and group projects, as well as conduct research on various topics related to Pancasila Education. This course is designed to provide students with a deeper understanding of the principles of Pancasila and its relevance to contemporary Indonesian society, as well as its role in shaping the national identity and culture of Indonesia. At the end of the course, students will have a solid understanding of Pancasila and its principles and will be able to apply this knowledge in various contexts, including their personal and professional lives. Additionally, students will be equipped with the skills needed to analyze, interpret and implement Pancasila within the society and communities.', 2, 0, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 06:16:23', '2023-01-20 06:16:23'),
('COM620304', 'INTERACTION SYSTEM', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Interaction System is a course that explores the design and development of interactive systems, including digital interfaces and human-computer interaction. This course covers the principles and theories of interaction design, user-centered design, and usability evaluation, as well as the latest tools and technologies for creating engaging, intuitive, and effective interactive systems. Students will learn to conduct user research, create wireframes and prototypes, and evaluate the usability and effectiveness of interactive systems through hands-on projects and case studies. Topics include mobile interfaces, web interfaces, wearables, virtual reality, and internet of things. By the end of the course, students will have the skills and knowledge to create interactive systems that are user-centered, functional, and aesthetically pleasing.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 06:16:57', '2023-01-20 06:16:57'),
('COM620305', 'EXPERT SYSTEM', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Expert Systems is a course that focuses on the design, development, and implementation of computer systems that mimic the decision-making abilities of human experts. The course covers the theory and applications of artificial intelligence, with a specific emphasis on expert systems, which are computer programs that use knowledge-based systems, rule-based systems, and reasoning to solve complex problems. Throughout the course, students will learn about the various components of expert systems, including knowledge representation, reasoning, and natural language processing. They will also learn about the different types of expert systems, such as decision support systems, diagnostic systems, and expert advisors.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 06:17:33', '2023-01-20 06:17:33'),
('COM620306', 'ADVANCED WEB PROGRAMMING', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Web Continuation is a course designed for individuals who have a basic understanding of web development and want to expand their skills and knowledge in the field. The course covers advanced topics such as responsive design, web performance optimization, and server-side programming. Throughout the course, students will learn how to create websites and web applications that adapt to different screen sizes and devices, as well as how to optimize their loading speed and performance. They will also learn about server-side technologies such as Node.js and PHP and how to use them to build dynamic web applications.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 06:18:10', '2023-01-20 06:18:10'),
('COM620307', 'CLOUD COMPUTING', 'Peminatan', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Cloud computing is a course that explores the concept of using remote servers, accessed via the internet, to store, manage and process data. The course covers the different types of cloud services available, such as infrastructure as a service (IaaS), platform as a service (PaaS) and software as a service (SaaS), and how they can be used to improve efficiency and scalability for businesses and organizations. Students will learn about the architecture and design of cloud systems, as well as the security and privacy concerns associated with cloud computing. The course will also cover the various tools and technologies used in cloud computing, such as virtualization and containerization, and how they can be used to manage and deploy applications in the cloud. Upon completion of the course, students will have a solid understanding of cloud computing and its applications, and will be equipped with the skills and knowledge to design, implement and manage cloud-based systems and services.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 06:18:51', '2023-01-20 06:18:51'),
('COM620308', 'ADVANCED MOBILE PROGRAMMING', 'Peminatan', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'The course Mobile Continuation is designed for individuals who have already completed a basic mobile application development course and are looking to continue their education in this field. This course covers advanced topics such as cross-platform development, mobile security, and mobile app monetization. Students will learn how to create and publish applications that can run on multiple mobile operating systems such as iOS and Android. They will also learn how to incorporate security features into their apps to protect user data and prevent hacking. Additionally, the course will cover strategies for monetizing mobile apps, such as in-app purchases and advertising. This course is ideal for anyone looking to enhance their skills in mobile app development and take their career to the next level.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 06:19:37', '2023-01-20 06:19:37'),
('COM620309', 'NATURAL LANGUAGE PROCESSING', 'Peminatan', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Natural Language Processing (NLP) is a field of study that focuses on the interaction between human language and computers. It uses techniques such as machine learning, artificial intelligence, and computational linguistics to analyze, understand, and generate human language. This course covers the fundamental concepts and techniques used in NLP, including text pre-processing, part-of-speech tagging, syntactic parsing, semantic analysis, and text generation. Students will learn to apply these techniques to real-world problems, such as sentiment analysis, text summarization, and machine translation. Through hands-on projects and assignments, students will gain practical experience in using NLP tools and libraries, such as NLTK, SpaCy, and Gensim. By the end of the course, students will have a solid understanding of NLP and the ability to apply it to solve real-world problems.', 2, 0, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 06:20:19', '2023-01-20 06:20:19'),
('COM620310', 'PATTERN RECOGNITION', 'Peminatan', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Pattern Recognition is a course that focuses on the study of algorithms and techniques used to identify patterns and structure in data. It covers various methods, including supervised and unsupervised learning, and statistical models used for data analysis and prediction. The course covers topics such as feature extraction, feature selection, clustering, and classification, and students will learn how to apply these techniques to real-world data sets. Throughout the course, students will also learn how to use popular tools such as Python and R for data analysis and visualization. By the end of the course, students will have a solid understanding of how to analyze and make predictions from data, as well as how to implement these techniques using industry-standard tools and libraries.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 06:21:07', '2023-01-20 06:21:07'),
('COM620311', 'GEOGRAPHIC INFORMATION SYSTEM', 'Peminatan', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Geographic Information System (GIS) is a course that teaches students the principles and techniques of using computer technology to create, manage, and analyze spatial data. This data can include information about the physical and human characteristics of a specific location, such as topography, land use, population demographics, and infrastructure. Throughout the course, students will learn how to use GIS software, including industry-standard programs like ArcGIS, to map and visualize data. They will also learn how to collect and integrate different types of data, such as satellite imagery, aerial photographs, and survey data, into a single GIS project.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 06:21:49', '2023-01-20 06:21:49'),
('COM620312', 'PROFESSIONAL ETHICS', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Professional ethics is a course that covers the principles and standards of conduct that govern the behavior of individuals and organizations in the professional realm. The course typically examines the ethical principles that apply to various professions, such as law, medicine, engineering, and business. It may also explore the moral and social responsibilities that come with being a professional, and the impact of professional conduct on society as a whole.', 2, 0, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 06:22:41', '2023-01-20 06:22:41'),
('COM620313', 'INTERNSHIP', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'An internship course is a hands-on learning experience that allows students to apply their knowledge and skills in a real-world setting. The course typically involves working with a company or organization to gain hands-on experience in a specific field or industry. During the internship, students will work on projects and tasks assigned by their supervisor, and will receive feedback and guidance on their work. The course is designed to provide students with an opportunity to gain practical experience, develop their professional skills, and make connections in their chosen field. The duration of an internship course vary depending on the institution, but it typically runs for several weeks or months. Some courses also include an additional academic component, such as a journal or reflection paper, to help students reflect on their experiences and learning.', 0, 3, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 06:31:40', '2023-01-20 06:31:40'),
('COM620314', 'DATA WAREHOUSE AND BIG DATA', 'Peminatan', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Data Warehouse and Big Data is a course that explores the concepts, techniques, and technologies related to the management and analysis of large and complex data sets. The course covers topics such as data warehousing, big data platforms, data mining, and data visualization. Students will learn how to design, implement, and maintain data warehouses, as well as how to use big data tools and technologies to extract insights from large data sets. The course also covers data governance and security issues, as well as the ethical considerations surrounding the use of big data. Students will have the opportunity to work on real-world projects, using industry-standard tools and technologies. By the end of the course, students will have a solid understanding of the key concepts and techniques involved in data warehousing and big data, and will be able to apply them in their professional careers.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 06:34:17', '2023-01-20 06:34:17'),
('COM620315', 'GRAPHICS COMPUTER', 'Peminatan', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'A Graphics Computer course is a course that focuses on the use of computer technology to create, manipulate, and display images and graphics. This can include topics such as computer-generated imagery (CGI), 3D modeling and animation, digital painting and drawing, and image editing and manipulation. The course may cover various software and tools used in the industry, including Adobe Photoshop, Illustrator, and After Effects, as well as industry-standard 3D software such as Maya, 3ds Max, and Blender. Students will learn how to use these tools to create digital artwork, animations, and visual effects for various applications such as video games, films, and digital media. Additionally, the course cover concepts such as color theory, lighting, and compositing.', 2, 0, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 06:35:03', '2023-01-20 06:35:03'),
('COM620316', 'INFORMATION SYSTEM SECURITY', 'Peminatan', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Information systems security (ISS) is a critical aspect of protecting an organization\'s information assets, and it is essential for students who are studying information systems to have a strong understanding of ISS concepts and practices.', 2, 0, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 06:35:45', '2023-01-20 06:35:45'),
('COM620317', 'IT PROJECT MANAGEMENT', 'Peminatan', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'The IT Project Management course is designed to provide students with the knowledge and skills necessary to effectively manage and deliver successful IT projects. This course covers the key principles and best practices of project management, including project planning, budgeting, risk management, and communication. Students will learn about the various project management methodologies, including Waterfall and Agile, and how to choose the best approach for a given project. The course will also cover how to identify and manage project stakeholders, as well as how to effectively communicate with team members and stakeholders throughout the project lifecycle.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 06:39:24', '2023-01-20 06:39:24'),
('COM620318', 'OPERATIONS RESEARCH', 'Peminatan', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'The course deals with the use of mathematical models for planning of corporate and governmental activities. Most of the planning problems will consist of an economic objective which we want to maximize under scarce resources. Operations Research consists of: - limiting and defining the current problem, - formulating a mathematical model of the problem, - calculating an optimal solution of the model, -and finally interpreting and implementing the found solution. This course deals with both deterministic and stochastic problems, and they will be analyzed based on the following models and methods: Linear and nonlinear programming, integer programming, network models, simple queuing theory and simulation. We will use spreadsheets to find numerical solutions for some of the analyzed problems.', 2, 0, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 06:40:06', '2023-01-20 06:40:06'),
('COM620319', 'INTRODUCTION TO ROBOTICS', 'Peminatan', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Introduction to Robotics is a course that provides a foundational understanding of the concepts, design, and programming of robots. The course covers the basic principles of robotics including kinematics, dynamics, and control systems. Students will learn about different types of robots and their applications, as well as the sensors and actuators used in robotics. They will also gain hands-on experience programming robots using various programming languages and frameworks. Additionally, the course will explore the ethical, societal, and economic implications of robots and their impact on the future. Overall, this course aims to provide a comprehensive understanding of the field of robotics for students interested in pursuing a career in this field or for those simply interested in learning more about the technology.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 06:40:49', '2023-01-20 06:40:49'),
('COM620320', 'SPECIAL PROJECT', 'Peminatan', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'The Special Project course is designed for students who are interested in pursuing a specific area of study or research in depth. This course allows students to engage in independent research and to apply the knowledge and skills they have acquired throughout their academic journey to a real-world problem or challenge. Students will work closely with a faculty advisor to develop a proposal for their project and to conduct research, gather data, and analyze their findings. The course will culminate in a final presentation of their project, which may include a written report, a poster presentation, or a formal presentation to a panel of experts. This course is ideal for students who are considering pursuing graduate studies or who are looking to gain real-world experience in a specific field.', 2, 0, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 06:41:25', '2023-01-20 06:41:25');
INSERT INTO `mks` (`kode`, `nama`, `rumpun`, `prasyarat`, `kurikulum`, `deskripsi`, `bobot_teori`, `bobot_praktikum`, `bahasa`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
('COM620321', 'INFORMATION RETRIEVAL', 'Peminatan', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Information Retrieval (IR) is a course that studies methods and techniques for efficiently retrieving relevant information from large collections of data. The course covers topics such as text indexing, query processing, ranking, and evaluation of retrieval systems. Students will learn about the underlying algorithms and data structures used in IR systems and gain hands-on experience through programming projects and assignments. The course will also cover advanced topics such as natural language processing, machine learning, and web search engines. This course is designed for students with a background in computer science, information science, or related fields and is essential for anyone interested in the field of information management and search technology.', 2, 0, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 07:17:45', '2023-01-20 07:17:45'),
('COM620401', 'CAPITA SELECTA', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Capita Selecta is a course that focuses on specialized topics within a specific field of study. These topics are chosen by the instructor and are designed to provide students with in-depth knowledge and understanding of a particular subject matter. The course content is usually more advanced than that of a regular course, and may include research, case studies, and hands-on projects. The course is ideal for students who are interested in pursuing a career in a particular field or for those who want to gain a deeper understanding of a specific topic. Additionally, students are expected to have a high level of motivation, discipline, and willingness to learn through independent research.', 2, 0, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 07:19:19', '2023-01-20 07:19:19'),
('COM620402', 'SPECIAL TASK', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, '\"Special tasks are short-term, focused assignments that computer science students can undertake to gain additional experience or learning opportunities.\r\nThese special tasks can provide computer science students with valuable experience and learning opportunities that can help them to develop new skills, explore new technologies, and network with other professionals in the field.\"', 1, 0, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 07:20:42', '2023-01-20 07:20:42'),
('COM620403', 'BIOINFORMATION', 'Peminatan', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Bioinformatics is a field that combines biology, computer science, and information technology to analyze and interpret biological data. This interdisciplinary course explores the use of computational tools and techniques for analyzing, interpreting, and visualizing large-scale biological data sets. Students will learn about the various bioinformatics methods used to analyze DNA, RNA, and protein sequences, as well as the use of databases and software for data management and analysis. Additionally, students will gain an understanding of current bioinformatics research and its applications in areas such as genomics, proteomics, and bioinformatics-based drug design. This course also includes hands-on experience using bioinformatics software, programming, and data analysis. Through a combination of lectures, labs, and projects, students will develop the necessary skills and knowledge to successfully analyze and interpret large-scale biological data sets.', 2, 0, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 07:21:27', '2023-01-20 07:21:27'),
('COM620404', 'BLOCKCHAIN AND CRYPTO CURRENCY', 'Peminatan', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Blockchain and Crypto Currency is a course that provides an in-depth understanding of the underlying technology of blockchain and its applications in the world of crypto currency. The course covers the fundamentals of blockchain technology, including its architecture, consensus mechanisms, and smart contract programming. Students will also learn about the different types of crypto currencies and their market dynamics, as well as the various use cases of blockchain technology in industries such as finance, supply chain management, and healthcare. The course will include hands-on exercises, case studies, and group projects to help students gain practical skills in blockchain development and crypto currency trading. By the end of the course, students will have a solid understanding of the technology and its potential impact on the global economy.', 2, 0, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 07:24:11', '2023-01-20 07:24:11'),
('COM620405', 'BUSINESS INTELLIGENCE', 'Peminatan', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Business Intelligence (BI) is a course that provides students with an in-depth understanding of the concepts, tools, and techniques used to collect, analyze, and present data in a business context. It covers topics such as data warehousing, data mining, data visualization, and reporting, as well as the use of BI software and platforms to support decision making and business strategy. The course also explores the role of BI in creating competitive advantages, identifying trends and opportunities, and managing risks and performance. Throughout the course, students will gain hands-on experience with BI software and technologies, and develop the skills to design and implement effective BI solutions for real-world business scenarios.', 2, 0, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 07:25:02', '2023-01-20 07:25:02'),
('COM620406', 'PARALLEL COMPUTING', 'Peminatan', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Parallel computing is a subject course that focuses on the theory and practice of designing and implementing algorithms and software for parallel and distributed computing systems. It covers a range of topics including parallel programming models, parallel algorithms, performance analysis and optimization, and the design and implementation of parallel systems. The course also explores the use of parallel computing in various application areas such as scientific computing, data analytics, machine learning, and high-performance computing. The goal of the course is to provide students with a solid understanding of the concepts and techniques needed to design, implement, and evaluate parallel systems and applications.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 07:25:43', '2023-01-20 07:25:43'),
('COM620407', 'COMPUTERS AND SOCIETY', 'Peminatan', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Computers and Society is a course that explores the impact of computers and technology on society. It covers a wide range of topics, including the history and evolution of computers, their impact on various aspects of society such as communication, education, business, and government, and the ethical and societal implications of these technologies. Students will learn about the latest trends and innovations in computer technology and their impact on society, and will also have the opportunity to engage in discussions and debates on relevant and timely topics. The course also covers the role of computers in shaping our culture, economy, and social interactions, and how these technologies are transforming the way we live, work, and communicate. Overall, the course is designed to provide a comprehensive understanding of the impact of computers on our society and the ways in which we interact with them.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 07:26:27', '2023-01-20 07:26:27'),
('COM620408', 'GAMES DESIGN', 'Peminatan', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Game design is the process of creating and developing the concept, mechanics, and rules for a game. It is the foundation upon which a game is built and encompasses various aspects of the game such as the gameplay, the story, the characters, the art, the audio, and the overall experience. There are several key competencies that students studying game design should aim to develop in order to be successful in the field Creativity, Technical Skills, Problem Solving, Communication and collaboration, Project management, Adaptability, Player-centered approach, Playtesting and Iteration, Game Design knowledge.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 07:27:07', '2023-01-20 07:27:07'),
('COM620409', 'AUGMENTED DAN VIRTUAL REALITY', 'Peminatan', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Augmented Reality and Virtual Reality is a subject course that focuses on the development and implementation of technology that enhances or creates a simulated experience for users. This includes the use of devices such as virtual reality headsets, smartphones, and tablets to create immersive and interactive environments. The course covers topics such as the history and development of AR and VR technology, programming and design techniques, and the use of these technologies in various industries such as gaming, education, and healthcare. Students will learn how to create and design augmented and virtual reality experiences, as well as how to evaluate the effectiveness of these technologies. The course also addresses the ethical and societal implications of AR and VR technology.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 07:27:52', '2023-01-20 07:27:52'),
('COM620447', 'RESEARCH PROPOSAL', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'A research proposal is a document that outlines a proposed research project and seeks funding or support for the project. It typically includes an introduction to the research topic, a literature review of existing studies, a statement of the research question or hypothesis, a description of the proposed research methods, a discussion of the potential significance and implications of the research, and a budget and timeline for the project. The proposal should be written in a clear and persuasive manner, and should demonstrate the importance and feasibility of the proposed research.', 0, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 07:36:51', '2023-01-20 07:36:51'),
('COM620448', 'RESEARCH RESULT', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Research results refer to the findings or outcomes of a research study. They can be presented in various forms such as tables, figures, and written text, and should be presented in a clear and concise manner. The results section of a research paper typically includes a summary of the data collected, an analysis of the findings, and a discussion of the implications of the results. It is important that the results are presented in a logical and unbiased manner, and that they are supported by the data collected during the research study. The results should also be placed in context by discussing how they relate to existing literature in the field.', 0, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 07:37:27', '2023-01-20 07:37:27'),
('COM620449', 'THESIS/FINAL PROJECT', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'A thesis is a long essay or dissertation that presents the author\'s research and findings on a specific topic. It is typically written as a requirement for an academic degree such as a master\'s or doctoral degree. The thesis should demonstrate the student\'s ability to conduct independent research and to present their findings in a clear and organized manner. A thesis typically includes an introduction, literature review, methodology, results, discussion, and conclusion. The introduction should provide background information on the topic and state the research question or hypothesis. The literature review should summarize existing research on the topic. The methodology should describe the research design and methods used to collect and analyze data. The results should present the findings of the research in a clear and concise manner. The discussion should interpret the results and relate them to existing literature in the field. The conclusion should summarize the main findings of the research and suggest directions for future research.', 0, 4, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 07:59:07', '2023-01-20 07:59:07'),
('MIP620101', 'BASIC SCIENCE', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Basic science is a broad field of study that encompasses many different subjects, including biology, chemistry, and physics. At its core, basic science is focused on understanding the fundamental principles and concepts that govern our natural world.', 2, 0, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 05:03:02', '2023-01-20 05:03:02'),
('UNI620101', 'ISLAMIC EDUCATION', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Islamic education is the process of acquiring knowledge and skills in the Islamic faith and its teachings. This can include instruction in areas such as Quranic studies, Hadith, Fiqh (Islamic jurisprudence), Seerah (biography of the Prophet Muhammad), Aqeedah (Islamic theology), and Tafsir (exegesis of the Quran). The goal of Islamic education is to help individuals gain a deeper understanding of their religion, to develop a personal relationship with God and to become better Muslims.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 05:04:30', '2023-01-20 05:04:30'),
('UNI620102', 'CATHOLIC EDUCATION', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, '\"Catholic education refers to the study and understanding of the teachings and principles of the Catholic Church, which is one of the main Christian denominations. It encompasses a wide range of subjects, including the Bible, the history of the Catholic Church, and the beliefs, practices, and values of the Catholic faith.\r\nThis education aims to help students understand the basic concepts and principles of Catholicism and how it has shaped the culture and society. It also provides an understanding of the Catholic way of life, its spiritual beliefs, practices, and sacraments. This education usually includes the study of the Bible and the teachings of Jesus, as well as the study of the history, theology and liturgical practices of the Catholic Church. It may also include the study of the social teachings of the Catholic Church, such as the role of the Church in society and the importance of social justice.\"', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 05:05:15', '2023-01-20 05:05:15'),
('UNI620103', 'CHRISTIAN EDUCATION', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, '\"Christian education refers to the study and understanding of the teachings and principles of Christianity. It encompasses a wide range of subjects, including the Bible, the history of Christianity, and the beliefs, practices, and values of the Christian faith.\r\nThis education aims to help students understand the basic concepts and principles of Christianity and how it has shaped the culture and society. It also provides an understanding of the Christian way of life and its spiritual beliefs and practices. This education usually includes the study of the New Testament and the teachings of Jesus, as well as the Old Testament and the history of Christianity. It may also include the study of Christian theology, ethics and the different denominational perspectives.\"', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 05:07:43', '2023-01-20 05:07:43'),
('UNI620104', 'HINDU EDUCATION', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Hindu education generally refers to the study and understanding of the teachings and principles of Hinduism. It encompasses a wide range of subjects, including the major texts and sacred scripture, the gods and goddesses of the Hindu pantheon, the history and development of Hinduism, and the philosophical and spiritual principles that underlie the tradition.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 05:12:11', '2023-01-20 05:12:11'),
('UNI620105', 'BUDDHA EDUCATION', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Buddhist education generally refers to the study and understanding of the teachings and principles of Buddhism. It encompasses a wide range of subjects such as the Four Noble Truths, the Eightfold Path, mindfulness, and the role of meditation in spiritual development. It also includes the study of the life and teachings of the historical Buddha, Siddhartha Gautama, as well as the history and development of Buddhism as a religion and philosophy.', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 05:15:43', '2023-01-20 05:15:43'),
('UNI620109', 'LOCAL ETHICS AND WISDOM EDUCATION', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Local ethics and wisdom education is a type of curriculum that focuses on teaching the ethical principles and traditional wisdom of a specific culture or community. This can include studying the customs, beliefs, and values that shape the way people live, as well as the moral codes that guide their behavior.', 2, 0, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 05:19:01', '2023-01-20 05:19:01'),
('UNI620306', 'INDONESIAN LANGUAGE EDUCATION', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Indonesian Language Education is a course designed to teach students the basics of the Indonesian language, culture, and customs. The course is aimed at students who have no previous knowledge of the language and is designed to be interactive, engaging and fun. Students will learn to speak, read, and write in Indonesian, as well as develop a deeper understanding of the culture and customs of Indonesia. The course covers topics such as basic grammar, vocabulary, sentence structure, and conversational phrases. Throughout the course, students will have the opportunity to practice their language skills through interactive activities, group discussions, and role-playing exercises. By the end of the course, students will have developed a solid foundation in the Indonesian language and will be able to communicate effectively with native speakers.', 2, 0, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 05:28:55', '2023-01-20 05:28:55'),
('UNI620307', 'CIVIC EDUCATION', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, 'Civic Education is a course that teaches students about their rights and responsibilities as citizens of a country. It covers a wide range of topics, including the history and structure of government, political systems, and the role of citizens in civic engagement. Students learn about the foundations of democracy and the importance of active participation in the democratic process. They explore the branches of government and the role of the judiciary, the legislative, and the executive branches in shaping public policy. Students also learn about political parties, elections, and the role of the media in shaping public opinion.', 2, 0, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 05:29:48', '2023-01-20 05:29:48'),
('UNI620401', 'COMMUNITY SERVICE PROGRAM', 'Wajib', 'Tidak ada', 2020, '\"Community service programs provide computer science students with an opportunity to use their skills and knowledge to make a positive impact on their local community. \r\nBy participating in community service programs, computer science students can apply their skills and knowledge to make a difference in their communities and gain valuable experience that can help them to grow professionally\"', 2, 1, 'Bahasa', '2023-01-20 07:28:43', '2023-01-20 07:28:43');
